The paper deals with information aggregation in sensor networks, which involves encoding and decoding strategies for computing functions of sensor measurements. This falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also studies the structure of the function and its effect on encoding strategies, which is related to data structures (cs.DS) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses interactive computation and message passing, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG).
